          "message": "I fixed the Copilot hook logging so turns are tracked reliably instead of by message text or by “last event in the whole transcript”. The prompt hook now assigns a stable `turn_index` and pulls attachments by prompt order, which prevents duplicate prompts from being matched to the wrong message in [.github/hooks/scripts/log-message.sh](.github/hooks/scripts/log-message.sh#L34). The response hook now uses the prompt/response counts already stored in the session log to isolate the current turn before extracting the assistant reply and tool calls in [.github/hooks/scripts/log-session-end.sh](.github/hooks/scripts/log-session-end.sh#L35).\n\nFor `fetch_webpage` specifically, the logging is proper now: non-heavy tools keep their parsed args, so `urls` and `query` are retained in `tool_calls`. I also updated the heavy-tool redaction list to match the tools you’re actually using, so mutating/file-heavy calls like `apply_patch` and `run_in_terminal` are logged with `args: null` instead of dumping large payloads in [.github/hooks/scripts/log-session-end.sh](.github/hooks/scripts/log-session-end.sh#L42).\n\nValidation: I ran `bash -n` on both scripts and a simulated two-turn transcript with identical prompts. The resulting log correctly recorded turn 1 as `response 1` with `fetch_webpage` args preserved, and turn 2 as `response 2` with `apply_patch` redacted.",
