          "message": "Everything is in place. Here's what was done:\n\n**Git tracking** (`A .github/logs/copilot-history.json` — now staged):\n- Added `!.github/logs/` and `!.github/logs/copilot-history.json` negation rules to `.gitignore` to override the `logs/` exclusion\n\n**Edit protection** (three layers):\n1. **OS permissions** — file is `444` (read-only for everyone); you must `chmod u+w` before any edit\n2. **`.gitattributes`** — file is marked `binary -diff -merge`, so git never diffs or auto-merges it\n3. **`.git/hooks/pre-commit`** — blocks commits where the history file changed unless a `.hook-staged` marker was created by the hook scripts; the hook scripts now `touch .hook-staged` before each `git add`, so their writes go through cleanly while manual edits are rejected",
